<doc>
  <member name="VMRDeinterlacePrefs">
    <summary>
      <para>The <b>VMRDeinterlacePrefs</b> enumeration type describes the deinterlacing method that the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/video-mixing-renderer-filter-7">Video Mixing Renderer Filter 7</a> (VMR-7) uses if the method set by the application cannot be used.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/DirectShow/directshow-enumerated-types">DirectShow Enumerated Types</seealso>
    <seealso cref="IVMRDeinterlaceControl Interface" />
  </member>
  <member name="VMRDeinterlacePrefs.DeinterlacePref_NextBest">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the next best mode offered by the driver.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="VMRDeinterlacePrefs.DeinterlacePref_BOB">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the bob method.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="VMRDeinterlacePrefs.DeinterlacePref_Weave">
    <summary>
      <para>Use the weave method (that is, no deinterlacing).</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="VMRDeinterlacePrefs.DeinterlacePref_Mask">
    <summary>
      <para>Bitwise <b>OR</b> of the previous flags. This value is not a valid flag.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>